			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2022</a> paper:</span><br><i>signatr: A Data-Driven Fuzzing Tool for R</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/AlexiTurcotte.html">Alexi Turcotte</a>, <a href="../profile/PierreDonatBouillud.html">Pierre Donat-Bouillud</a>, <a href="../profile/FilipKřikava.html">Filip Křikava</a>, <a href="../profile/JanVítek.html">Jan Vítek</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3567512.3567530">10.1145/3567512.3567530</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5c.html"><span class="tagM">T5C: Testing</span></a><ul><li> signatr is a fuzzing/testing tool aimed at automatically finding bugs in R programs.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3d.html"><span class="tagL">T3D: GPLs</span></a><ul><li> It targets the general-purpose language R and its dynamic-language ecosystem.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> The contribution includes dedicated tooling to generate inputs and drive fuzzing campaigns.
</li></ul></li></ul>
